{
  "id": "tapestry-delegation-routing-mixed-category-parallel-batch",
  "title": "Tapestry delegates parallel tasks to different category shuttles simultaneously",
  "description": "Checks that when two parallel-safe tasks match different categories, Tapestry delegates both in the same response using their respective category shuttle agents.",
  "phase": "experimental",
  "tags": ["experimental", "tapestry", "delegation-routing", "category", "parallelism"],
  "target": {
    "kind": "builtin-agent-prompt",
    "agent": "tapestry"
  },
  "executor": {
    "kind": "model-response",
    "provider": "openrouter",
    "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-20250514",
    "input": "You are executing /start-work. The following category agents are available:\n- shuttle-frontend: patterns [*.tsx, *.css, src/components/**]\n- shuttle-backend: patterns [*.go, src/api/**]\n- shuttle: fallback for unmatched tasks\n\nThe plan has 2 unchecked tasks:\n\n- [ ] Task 1/4: Add UserCard component\n  **Files**: src/components/UserCard.tsx\n  **What**: Create a React component for displaying user info\n  **Acceptance**: UserCard renders name and email props\n\n- [ ] Task 2/4: Add user API endpoint\n  **Files**: src/api/users.go\n  **What**: Add GET /api/users/:id endpoint\n  **Acceptance**: Endpoint returns user JSON with 200 status\n\nHow would you delegate these tasks? Can they run in parallel?"
  },
  "evaluators": [
    {
      "kind": "llm-judge",
      "expectedAnyOf": [
        "shuttle-frontend and shuttle-backend in parallel",
        "delegate to shuttle-frontend and shuttle-backend simultaneously",
        "route Task 1 to shuttle-frontend and Task 2 to shuttle-backend in the same response",
        "Task 1 to shuttle-frontend and Task 2 to shuttle-backend concurrently"
      ],
      "forbiddenContains": ["sequential", "one at a time", "wait for", "generic shuttle", "plain shuttle"]
    }
  ]
}
